%2C200%20people%20of%20total%2055%2C000%20population%20are%20at%20risk%20of%20having%20their%20homes%20tip%20into%20the%20widening%20abyss.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20space%20of%20the%20last%20few%20months%2C%20the%20dimensions%20have%20expanded%20exponentially%2C%20approaching%20substantially%20closer%20to%20the%20residences%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20emergency%20decree%20issued%20by%20the%20city%20government%20earlier%20this%20month%20said%20about%20the%20sinkholes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20buildings%20have%20already%20been%20destroyed%2C%20the%20decree%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20sinkholes%20are%20an%20escalation%20of%20a%20problem%20that%20residents%20of%20Buriticupu%2C%20in%20Maranhao%20state%2C%20have%20been%20watching%20unfold%20for%20the%20last%2030%20years%2C%20as%20rains%20slowly%20erode%20soils%20made%20vulnerable%20by%20their%20sandy%20nature%2C%20plus%20a%20combination%20of%20poorly%20planned%20building%20work%20and%20deforestation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20large%20soil%20erosions%20are%20known%20in%20Brazil%20as%20%26quot%3Bvocoroca%26quot%3B%2C%20a%20word%20of%20indigenous%20origins%20that%20means%20%26quot%3Bto%20tear%20the%20earth%26quot%3B%20and%20is%20the%20equivalent%20of%20sinkholes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20becomes%20worse%20in%20periods%20of%20heavy%20rain%20such%20as%20the%20current%20one%2C%20says%20Marcelino%20Farias%2C%20a%20geographer%20and%20professor%20at%20the%20Federal%20University%20of%20Maranhao.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAntonia%20dos%20Anjos%2C%20who%20has%20lived%20in%20Buriticupu%20for%2022%20years%2C%20fears%20more%20sinkholes%20will%20soon%20appear.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20this%20danger%20right%20in%20front%20of%20us%2C%20and%20nobody%20knows%20where%20this%20hole%20has%20been%20opening%20up%20underneath%2C%26quot%3B%20the%2065%20year%20old%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBuriticupu%20secretary%20of%20public%20works%2C%20and%20an%20engineer%2C%20Lucas%20Conceicao%20said%20the%20municipality%20clearly