3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20always%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fap-more-sleep-in-seattle-later-school-start-helps-kids-get-zzz-2018-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eencourage%20them%20to%20sleep%20as%20much%20as%20possible%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20because%20I%20believe%20that%20sleep%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20things%20they%20need%2C%20especially%20at%20their%20age.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20parents%20might%20disagree%20with%20me%20and%20encourage%20strict%20wake-ups%2C%20even%20over%20the%20summer%2C%20but%20in%20our%20family%2C%20my%20teenagers%20can't%20possibly%20get%20anywhere%20near%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fsleep-cycle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erecommended%20hours%20of%20sleep%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20a%20regular%20basis.%20Between%20school%2C%20sports%2C%20work%2C%20and%20family%20commitments%2C%20most%20nights%20they%20are%20lucky%20to%20get%20six%20to%20seven%20hours%2C%20and%20if%20I'm%20being%20honest%2C%20some%20nights%20it's%20even%20less%20than%20that.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI'm%20aware%20of%20the%20science%20that%20says%20that%20teens'%20brains%20are%20wired%20to%20stay%20up%20later%20and%20sleep%20in%2C%20but%20unfortunately%2C%20our%20school%20district%20%E2%80%94%20like%20many%20%E2%80%94%20just%20can't%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fschools-in-us-should-started-later-itd-improve-academic-performance-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eaccommodate%20a%20schedule%20that%20supports%20their%20sleep%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20We%20live%20in%20a%20rural%20area%20where%20a%20lot%20of%20kids%20depend%20on%20busing%2C%20so%20the%20bus%20schedule%20dictates%20the%20school%20schedule%2C%20which%20means%20very%20early%20wake-up%20times.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2272fd017f-951b-45dc-a8b3-6c2ac02eea53%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20are%20not%20lazy%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere's%20not%20a%20lot%20I%20can%20do%20to%20create%20more%20hours%20of%20sleep%20for%20them%20at%20night%20during%20the%20school%20year%2C%20but%20what%20I%20do%20is%20always%20encourage%20them%20to%20sleep%20as%20much%20as%20they%20want%20all%20other%20days%20of%20the%20year.%20I've%20heard%20people%20call%20teens%20lazy%20for%20sleeping%20in%20so%20much%2C%20but%20to%20me%2C%20it's%20about%20supporting%20their%20health%20in%20a%20very%20basic%20way.%20I%20want%20my%20teens%20to%20understand%20and%20emphasize%20the%20importance%20of%20sleep%2C%20especially%20as%20they%20grow%20into%20adults.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPart%20of%20my%20motivation%20is%20also%20selfish.%20I%20am%20personally%20someone%20who%20has%20always%20needed%20a%20lot%20of%20sleep%20to%20function%2C%20so%20just%20in%20case%20they%20turn%20out%20like%20me%2C%20I%20want%20them%20to%20know%20it's%20okay%20to%20be%20someone%20who%20needs%20a%20lot%20of%20sleep.%20Years%20of%20sleep%20deprivation%20as%20a%20mother%20severely%20impacted%20my%20physical%20and%20mental%20health%2C%20yet%20I've%20always%20felt%20guilty%20anytime%20I%20needed%20more%20sleep%20or%20%26quot%3Blet%26quot%3B%20my%20husband%20help%20me%20at%20night.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20far%2C%20my%20strategy%20is%20working.%20My%20teens%20are%20responsible%2C%20do%20well%20in%20school%2C%20work%20side%20jobs%20when%20they%20want%20spending%20money%2C%20and%20have%20no%20problem%20regulating%20their%20own%20sleep.%20I%20do%20set%20some%20boundaries%20that%20I%20also%20use%20to%20support%20a%20healthy%20sleep%20environment%3A%20their%20phones%20have%20auto%20bedtimes%20that%20I%20control%20(weekdays%20have%20earlier%20times%20than%20weekends)%2C%20their%20bedrooms%20are%20kept%20screen-free%2C%20and%20I%20instituted%20white%20noise%20habits%20fr