t.%20The%20X-37%20project%20was%20transferred%20to%20the%20Defense%20Advanced%20Research%20Projects%20Agency%20in%202004%20and%20became%20classified%20because%20of%20its%20military%20applications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202006%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdetails-about-air-force-space-plane-that-spent-2-years-in-space-2017-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fa%3E%20announced%20the%20development%20of%20its%20own%20variant%20of%20the%20space%20plane%2C%20known%20as%20the%20X-37B%2C%20designed%20to%20operate%20with%20an%20orbital%20speed%20of%20nearly%2017%2C500%20mph%20for%20up%20to%20270%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20uncrewed%20test%20vehicle%20was%20nearly%2030%20feet%20long%20and%20had%20a%20wingspan%20of%20about%2015%20feet.%20Its%20max%20takeoff%20weight%20was%2011%2C000%20pounds%2C%20and%20it%20could%20accommodate%20payloads%20of%20up%20to%20500%20pounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDubbed%20the%20%26quot%3Bmost%20advanced%20re-entry%20spacecraft%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20X-37B%20program%20would%20focus%20on%20%26quot%3Brisk%20reduction%2C%20experimentation%2C%20and%20operational%20concept%20development%20for%20reusable%20space%20vehicle%20technologies%2C%20in%20support%20of%20long-term%20developmental%20space%20objectives%2C%26quot%3B%20then-Air%20Force%20Secretary%20Michael%20Wynne%20said%20in%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EExperimenting%20in%20space%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20X-37B%20Orbital%20Test%20Vehicle%20en%20route%20to%20the%20staging%20area%20ahead%20of%20its%20launch.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b8b7f9c832c3638fa4e3bb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20X-37B%20Orbital%20Test%20Vehicle%20en%20route%20to%20the%20staging%20area%20ahead%20of%20its%20launch.%3Cp%3ESenior%20Airman%20Timothy%20Kirchner%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20X-37B%20was%20tasked%20with%20multiple%20orbital%20missions%2C%20ranging%20from%20testing%20materials%20under%20the%20conditions%20of%20space%20to%20releasing%20a%20small%20satellite%20with%20its%20own%20experimental%20payloads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20X-37B%20vehicle%20was%20launched%20into%20orbit%20from%20Cape%20Canaveral%20in%20April%202010.%20The%20test%20vehicle%20spent%20225%20days%20in%20space%20and%20returned%20in%20December%202010%20after%20conducting%20several%20orbit%20changes%2C%20though%20the%20data%20it%20collected%20during%20its%20maiden%20mission%20was%20classified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20the%20X-37B's%20sixth%20mission%20involved%20toting%20a%20small%20service%20module%20into%20space%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20The%20FalconSat-8%20was%20a%20small%20satellite%20developed%20by%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%20Academy%20carrying%20five%20experimental%20payloads.%20After%20a%20record-breaking%20908%20days%20in%20space%2C%20the%20X-37B%20completed%20its%20mission%20and%20landed%20at%20the%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center%20in%20November%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20much%20of%20the%20X-37B%20program%20is%20classified%2C%20the%20secrecy%20fueled%20speculation%20about%20the%20purpose%20of%20its%20mission%20sets%2C%20with%20some%20speculating%20that%20the%20space%20plane%20could%20be%20a%20weapons%20platform%20or%20used%20for%20intelligence%2C%20surveillance%2C%20and%20reconnaissance%20from%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ELaunched%20from%20a%20SpaceX%20rocket%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20front%20view%20of%20the%20nose%20of%20the%20X-37B%20following%20its%20landing%20at%20NASA's%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b8b7f9c832c3638fa4e3b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20front%20view%20of%20the%20nose%20of%20the%20X-37B%20following%20its%20landing%20at%20NASA's%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20courtesy%20photo%3C%2Fp