0gear%20surrounded%20the%20X-37B%20after%20it%20landed%20on%20the%20runway%20at%20NASA's%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b8b7f9c040bd1b4ca2d15e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22646%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPersonnel%20wearing%20protective%20gear%20surrounded%20the%20X-37B%20after%20it%20landed%20on%20the%20runway%20at%20NASA's%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20courtesy%20photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20image%20taken%20by%20its%20onboard%20camera%20shows%20just%20a%20small%20portion%20of%20the%20X-37B%2C%20few%20photos%20of%20the%20vehicle%20itself%20are%20available%20to%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20video%20montage%20posted%20on%20X%20in%202023%20included%20a%20blink-and-you'll-miss-it%20moment%20of%20the%20X-37B%20separating%20from%20its%20service%20module%20during%20its%20sixth%20mission%20in%202020.%20The%20US%20military%20and%20Boeing%20also%20released%20the%20first%20photos%20from%20the%20same%20mission%20after%20it%20was%20completed%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWatch%20Falcon%20Heavy%20launch%20the%20USSF-52%20mission%20to%20orbit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Fzrk4JcZ9Pt%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Fzrk4JcZ9Pt%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20SpaceX%20(%40SpaceX)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FSpaceX%2Fstatus%2F1740535676519821537%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EDecember%2029%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20US'%20X-37B%20vs.%20China's%20Shenlong%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Plumes%20of%20smoke%20erupted%20beneath%20the